amateur /ˈæmətə, -tʃʊə/

(amateurs) 

1. N-COUNT An amateur is someone who does something as a hobby and not as a job. 业余爱好者 

例： Jerry is an amateur who dances because he feels like it. 杰瑞是一位业余舞蹈爱好者，他跳舞因为他喜欢跳。 

2. ADJ Amateur sports or activities are done by people as a hobby and not as a job. 业余的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...professional athletes and amateur runners. …专业运动员和业余赛跑运动员。

</div>

